      <hedline>
        <hl1>BRAZIL SHOWS BIG SURPLUS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Jennifer L. Rich</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Rich, Jennifer L</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Brazil's budget surplus rose to record in March, reflecting government's efforts to control spending; surplus rose to $3.1 billion, compared with $2.1 billion in February; for first quarter, Brazil posts $7.4 billion primary surplus, almost doubling target of $3.95 billion agreed upon with International Monetary Fund (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Brazil's budget surplus rose to a record in March, reflecting the government's efforts to control spending. The surplus, which excludes interest payments, rose to $3.1 billion last month, compared with $2.1 billion in February. For the first quarter, Brazil posted a $7.4 billion primary surplus, almost doubling the target of $3.95 billion agreed upon with the International Monetary Fund.</p>
        <p>Jennifer L. Rich</p>
      </block>
